### CRUD Express API - Master Test Suite
###
### Instructions:
### 1. Start the server: pnpm run dev
### 2. Register a user first (see auth.rest)
### 3. Login to get a JWT token
### 4. Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE in each .rest file with your actual token
### 5. Run requests in order as some depend on previous responses
###
### Test Files:
### - auth.rest       : Authentication (register, login, whoami)
### - users.rest      : User management (CRUD operations)
### - categories.rest : Category management (CRUD operations)
### - products.rest   : Product management (CRUD with category filter)
### - orders.rest     : Order management (CRUD with status flow)
###
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api/v1

###
### Quick Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/../

###
### Auth Flow Example
### Step 1: Register
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Test User",
    "username": "testuser",
    "password": "testpass123"
}

###
### Step 2: Login (extract token)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "joni",
    "password": "admin123"
}
